# Digest and Stats.xml – Technical Reference

Reference for digest generation, meter lookup, and 30-day meter tables. Use when modifying score display, meter parsing, or Stats.xml handling.

## Data Flow Overview

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    subgraph NewScores [New high scores]
        Diff[Stats.xml diff] --> ParseDiff[Get-NewScoreEntriesFromStatsDiff]
        ParseDiff --> MeterLookup[Get-MeterFromSongChart]
        MeterLookup --> DigestEntry[Digest line with meter]
    end
    
    subgraph AllScores [All songs completed]
        Upload[Save/Upload XML files] --> ParseUpload[Get-MeterTallyFromUploadFolder]
        ParseUpload --> FilterDate1[DateTime >= cutoff]
        FilterDate1 --> MeterLookup1[Get-MeterFromSongChart]
        MeterLookup1 --> Tally[30-day meter table]
        Stats[Full Stats.xml] --> ParseStats[Get-MeterTallyFromStatsXml]
        ParseStats --> FilterDate2[DateTime >= cutoff]
        FilterDate2 --> MeterLookup2[Get-MeterFromSongChart]
        Digest[Digest files] --> ParseDigest[Get-MeterTallyFromDigests]
    end
```

## Digest Entries (New High Scores)

**Source:** Git diff of `LocalProfiles/*/Stats.xml` between backup runs.

**Flow:**
1. `Get-NewScoreEntriesFromStatsDiff` parses the diff for `<Song Dir="...">` blocks with `<Steps>` and `<HighScore>`.
2. For each new score, calls `Get-MeterFromSongChart` with `SongDir`, `Difficulty`, `StepsType`.
3. Formats as `**Player** set a new score for **Song** (Pack) - Difficulty (Meter) - X% on date.`

**Repair:** `Repair-DigestMeters` runs after digest write. For lines missing meters, uses the pack and song already printed in the digest line (`**Song** (Pack)`) to find the song folder on the machine. Flow: `Parse-DigestScoreLineForMeterRepair` extracts Pack and SongTitle from the line → `Get-SongFolderByPackAndName` searches `InstallPath\Songs`, `AdditionalSongs`, and `AdditionalSongFolderPaths` for `Pack\SongFolder` → `Get-MeterFromSongFolder` reads `.ssc` files inside and matches Difficulty + StepsType to return `#METER`. Supports both formats: new (`Difficulty - X% on date` or `Difficulty on date`) and legacy (`Difficulty, dance-single - X% DP on date` or `Difficulty, dance-single on date`).

## Meter Lookup

**Functions:** `Get-MeterFromSongChart`, `Get-MeterFromSongFolder`, `Get-SongFolderByPackAndName`

**Path resolution order:**
1. `InstallPath + SongDir` (e.g. `C:\ITGMania\Songs\Pack\Song`)
2. For `AdditionalSongs/` prefix: each path from `AdditionalSongFolderPaths` + suffix
3. If no `Songs/` or `AdditionalSongs/` prefix: try `InstallPath\Songs\SongDir`
4. **Fallback:** `Get-SongFolderByPackAndName` – search for `Pack/SongFolder` across all song roots (Songs, AdditionalSongs, AdditionalSongFolderPaths). Matches exact, StartsWith, or Contains.

**AdditionalSongFolderPaths:** From `config.json` `AdditionalSongFolderPaths` array, or parsed from `Preferences.ini` `AdditionalSongFolders` (Save folder, AppData, install root).

**Chart parsing:**
- **.ssc:** `#NOTEDATA:` blocks with `#STEPSTYPE`, `#DIFFICULTY`, `#METER`
- **.sm:** `#NOTES:` section. Standard format: `dance-single:`, `:`, `Medium:`, `8:` (type, description, difficulty, meter). Compact format: type, difficulty, meter. Parser tries both.

**Get-SongDisplayNameFromDir:** Splits `SongDir` on both `/` and `\` to extract Pack (second-to-last) and SongTitle (last). Handles Windows backslash paths.

## 30-Day Meter Tables

**Data flow priority:** Upload (all plays) → Stats.xml (top scores per chart) → Digests (new high scores only).

**Primary source – Upload folder:** StepMania writes one XML file per play to `Save/Upload/` (files named `yyyy-mm-dd nnnnn`). `Get-MeterTallyFromUploadFolder` enumerates `SavePortable/Upload/` and `SaveAppData/Upload/`, parses each file for `//HighScoreForASongAndSteps`, filters by `DateTime >= CutoffDate`, looks up meter via `Get-MeterFromSongChart`, and builds `@{ PlayerName => @{ Meter => Count } }`. Counts **all plays**, not just top scores. Player identification: `Name` from HighScore, or `PlayerGuid` mapped to profile name via `Get-PlayerGuidToNameMap` (reads `GeneralData/Guid` from LocalProfiles Stats.xml). Skips files by `LastWriteTime < CutoffDate` before parsing.

**Fallback – Stats.xml:** `Get-MeterTallyFromStatsXml` parses `SavePortable/LocalProfiles/*/Stats.xml` and `SaveAppData/LocalProfiles/*/Stats.xml`. Iterates `//Song` → `Steps` → `HighScoreList/HighScore`. Filters by `DateTime >= CutoffDate`. StepMania stores only the top N scores per chart, so this is not all plays.

**Fallback – Digests:** When both Upload and Stats.xml return empty for a player, `Get-MeterTallyFromDigests` parses digest lines (requires `Difficulty (Meter)` format) from the last 30 digest files. Counts new high scores only.

**Profile name:** From `Name` in HighScore (Upload), root `<Name>` in Stats.xml, or `"Profile " + profileId` if empty.

## Stats.xml Structure

```xml
<Stats>
  <Name>ProfileName</Name>
  <SongScores>
    <Song Dir="Songs/Pack/SongFolder">
      <Steps Difficulty="Challenge" StepsType="dance-single">
        <HighScoreList>
          <HighScore>
            <DateTime>2024-01-15T12:30:00</DateTime>
            ...
          </HighScore>
        </HighScoreList>
      </Steps>
    </Song>
  </SongScores>
</Stats>
```

## Upload XML Structure

```xml
<Stats>
  <RecentSongScores>
    <HighScoreForASongAndSteps>
      <Song Dir="Songs/Pack/SongFolder"/>
      <Steps Difficulty="Challenge" StepsType="dance-single"/>
      <HighScore>
        <Name>PlayerName</Name>
        <DateTime>2024-01-15T12:30:00</DateTime>
        <PlayerGuid>optional-profile-guid</PlayerGuid>
        ...
      </HighScore>
    </HighScoreForASongAndSteps>
  </RecentSongScores>
</Stats>
```

